items.title: German Pointers, Sandy Park Inn | Drewsteignton, Devon • Helen Duvall
items.description:
Screaming Abdabs Gallery posted a photo:

German Pointers, Sandy Park Inn | Drewsteignton, Devon • Helen Duvall. These two exceptionally fit German short-haired Pointers (GSP) were mesmerized by the moths which fluttered around the wall light in the doorway of The Sandy Park Inn, Chagford on a hot summer’s night. German pointers are a versatile and extremely agile breed of dog suitable for hunting on both land and water. They have webbed feet and are known for pursuing water fowl in rivers and lakes. This pair had long elegant muzzles which were also broad and strong, allowing them to retrieve larger game. Their deep brown eyes were particularly desirable, as their antics in the pub doorway were particularly amusing!
